President Obama has announced the recipients of the Presidential Award for Excellence in Science, Mathematics, and Engineering Mentoring (PAESMEM). This award recognizes individuals and organizations that play a crucial role in mentoring students studying science and engineering, particularly those from underrepresented groups. The mentors selected for this award will be honored at a White House ceremony and will receive a $10,000 award from the National Science Foundation. The recipients include educators from various universities and institutions across the United States. President Obama praised these mentors for their dedication to cultivating future scientists, engineers, and mathematicians and for opening new opportunities for their students.